      "content": "The Civil Rights Movement in the US was a pivotal period of American history, marked by the struggle for racial equality and justice. Key milestones include: the Montgomery Bus Boycott (1955-1956), led by Martin Luther King Jr., the March on Washington (1963), where King delivered his iconic \"I Have a Dream\" speech, the passage of the Civil Rights Act (1964) and Voting Rights Act (1965), and the Selma to Montgomery Marches (1965), which highlighted the brutal suppression of African American rights. These events ultimately led to the desegregation of public facilities, employment, and voting rights, but the struggle for true equality and justice continues to this day.",
